# LISA design — do not deviate

- **Design bible:** `docs/LISA_DESIGN_BIBLE.md`. Read it for every UI/design change.
- **Aesthetic:** "Midnight Folio" — dark room (--void, --room, --desk), gold lamp accent (--lamp), warm ink text (--ink). No chat bubbles, no pure white, no Inter/Roboto.
- **Typography:** Display = Cormorant Garamond; Body = Satoshi (fallback DM Sans); Mono = IBM Plex Mono.
- **Gold** = Lisa's identity, CTAs, focus, active state, chart/data emphasis. Use sparingly and meaningfully.
- **Components:** No Material/Chakra/Ant. Custom or shadcn fully restyled. Lucide icons only (no emoji in chrome).
- **Motion:** Under 300ms except ambient lamp (3s) and progress shimmer (1.8s). Respect prefers-reduced-motion.
- When editing CSS or React UI, align with the tokens, typography scale, and component specs in the design bible.
